In class notes

  • Data verbs -> input = data tables, output = data tables
  • Reduction verbs -> input = variables, single number/measure
  • Transformation verv -> input = variable, output = new variable

6- data verbs: deeplyedR? 1. summarise() -> allows to take datatable and reduce to single case 2. group_by() -> tell the systems to do other operations by given groups 3. filter() -> select out certain cases 4. mutate() -> apply a transformation verb 5. select() -> select certain variables that are of interested to you 6. arrange() -> re-order things 7. join

  group_by(color) %>%
  summarise(mean(carat)) %>%
